{'id': '2607.07846', 'categories': ['cs.AI', 'cs.CY'], 'pdf': 'https://arxiv.org/pdf/2607.07846', 'abs': 'https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.07846', 'authors': ['Ryan Duke'], 'title': 'VectorizationLLM: Smart Vectorization Based AI Assistant', 'comment': '44 pages, 6 figures', 'summary': 'VectorizationLLM is a specialized Large Language Model based on Google open-weight LLMs. The model is designed to assist students to learn smart vectorization, time/wave vector analysis, piecewise functions, Fourier analysis, and differential equations in MATLAB. The course application is CTEC 247: Applied Computational Analysis II by the Department of Electrical & Computer Engineering Technology at New York Institute of Technology Old Westbury. The LLM model is designed to be an instructive assistant, providing detailed explanations of concepts with examples from in-class notes without providing direct answers to questions. The model is designed with a RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation) knowledge base and system prompt architecture. Examples in both code, text, and images are provided in the LLM responses.'}
